            <para>Ra = Rear axle ratio which can normally be found on the rear axle housing or on the lineset ticket.
                With a 2-speed axle use the high range ratio.
            </para>
            <para>N = The number of teeth on the transmission speedometer output gear. International installed
                transmissions, including Allison have 16 teeth on the speedometer output gear.
            </para>
            <para>EXAMPLE:</para>
            <para>If a vehicle has 10 x 22 tires and 3.70:1 rear axle:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Refer to the table, the revolutions per mile (M) = 476.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The formula is PPM = M x Ra x N</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>PPM = 476 x 3.70 x 16 = 28179</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>The new pulses per mile then is programmed into the ECM using the Prolink EST. The Caterpillar ECM
                will accept a number between 1716 PPM and 65,535 PPM.
            </para>
